  "task": "\nYou are controlling a Windows Server 2019 desktop with Sage 200 installed.\nThe display is 1024x768. The interface is in Spanish.\n\nCURRENT STATE: Sage 200 login window is open. You need to log in first.\n\nYOUR MISSION: Log into Sage 200 and navigate to the development console to create a table.\n\nSTEP BY STEP:\n1. The login screen shows Usuario=Administrador. Type the password: Control1234\n   - Click on the password field (Contrase\u00f1a)\n   - Type: Control1234\n   - Click Aceptar button\n\n2. Once logged in, you should see the Sage 200 main interface.\n   Describe what you see.\n\n3. Navigate to: Consola de Administracion (Administration Console)\n   - Look in the top menu bar or sidebar for this option\n   - It may be under a menu like Herramientas (Tools) or Administracion\n\n4. In the Administration Console, go to: Herramientas > Tablas (Tools > Tables)\n   - This is where you can create new database tables\n\n5. Create a new table called CF_Equipos with these fields:\n   - CodigoEquipo (Character, 5 chars, Primary Key)\n   - Nombre (Character, 50 chars)  \n   - JuegaEuropa (Logico/Boolean)\n   - Competicion (Character, 30 chars)\n\n6. Save the table.\n\nTIPS:\n- After each action, wait for the UI to respond\n- The interface is entirely in Spanish\n- If you see a dialog or popup, read it carefully before acting\n- Password is: Control1234\n- If something doesnt work, try an alternative approach\n",
